    "summary": "Experienced computational physicist with strong research and computation skills. Extensive academic experience in theoretical materials science \u2013 structure prediction and property-characterization in diverse materials \u2013 based on state-of-the-art quantum, and multi-physics modeling and simulations. Strong background in method, algorithm, and technical development within solid-state physics and quantum chemistry tools directed to materials design and discovery. Proficient in transforming ideas into scientific projects, building research strategies, people/project management, and scientific dissemination. \n\n\nModeling & simulation: Density functional theory, many-body physics (Continuous Time Quantum Monte Carlo & Exact Diagonalisation solvers), quantum transport (Non-Equilibrium Greens\u2019 Function). \nComputation: Python, Fortran, \nData analysis & visualization: MATLAB, Mathematica, Gnuplot, Materials studio, Atomistic visualization software.\nMaterials Research: Molecular electronics & spintronics, strongly correlated electron systems, organic semiconductors, magnetic memory materials. \nCommunications: 30 papers in leading journals, 4 book chapters, over 20 invites, and contributed talks at international conferences. \nLeadership: mentored and co-mentored multiple Ph.D., master's, and bachelor's students at Uppsala Univ., \u00c9cole Polytechnique, Trinity College Dublin. Enjoys technical mentorship. Gave presentations in workshops and took technical hands-on sessions (Uppsala University, TU Wien).\nList of publications: https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=2cGaAHUAAAAJ&hl=en",
